DRUGA antagonize the effects of DRUGB .
Anticholinergics	group	antiglaucoma agents	group
effect

DRUGA in the presence of increased intraocular pressure may be hazardous when taken concurrently with agents such as DRUGB .
Anticholinergic drugs	group	corticosteroids	group
effect

DRUGA may affect gastrointestinal absorption of various drugs , such as slowly dissolving dosage forms of DRUGB ;
Anticholinergic agents	group	digoxin	drug
mechanism

DRUGA may antagonize the effects of drugs that alter gastrointestinal motility , such as DRUGB .
Anticholinergic drugs	group	metoclopramide	drug
effect

Because DRUGA may interfere with the absorption of DRUGB , simultaneous use of these drugs should be avoided .
antacids	group	anticholinergic agents	group
mechanism

CYP dgAdg Inhibitors ( e.g . DRUGA and DRUGB ) There have been rare reports of serious adverse events in connection with the coadministration of certain DRUGN ( e.g . DRUGN and DRUGN ) and potent CYP dgAdg inhibitors , resulting in vasospasm leading to cerebral ischemia and / or ischemia of the extremities .

DRUGA : Excessive reductions in blood pressure may occur in patients on diuretic therapy when DRUGB are started .
Diuretics	group	ACE inhibitors	group
false

The possibility of hypotensive effects with DRUGA can be minimized by discontinuing diuretic therapy for several days or cautiously increasing salt intake before initiation of treatment with DRUGN . If this is not possible , the starting dose of DRUGB should be reduced..

DRUGN may interact with the following drugs : DRUGN and other DRUGN ( may lower DRUGN levels ) , DRUGN ( bioavailability of oral DRUGN is increased with coadministration ) , DRUGN ( may decrease DRUGN levels ) , DRUGN dgdgdg ( reports of psychotic episodes when coadministered ) , DRUGN ( coadministration of DRUGN with DRUGN can inhibit ovarian function in women ) , DRUGN dgdg and other sedating drugs ( may result in additive sedation and an increased incidence of adverse effects ) , and DRUGN ( coadministration of DRUGA and DRUGN may interfere with the efficacy of the DRUGB ) .
